So, how do you create a bootable USB stick under Linux with Windows 10 on it?
# USB Device DEVICE=/dev/sdX # Delete every bit on it dd if=/dev/zero of=$DEVICE bs=1M count=1 # Create new partition fdisk ${DEVICE} n p 1 ENTER ENTER t c a w # Format and mount mkfs.vfat ${DEVICE}1 mount ${DEVICE}1 /mnt/ # Copy data mkdir Win10 mount -o loop Win10_1709_German_x64.
